<P>I don't care,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Vexat.</NOTE> if there were <HI>&s;ix bu&s;hels</HI> of <HI>catechi&s;ms.</HI> That is not what I <HI>want.</HI> I am. . .</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Nev.</SPEAKER>
<P>Perhaps you want to know whether the <HI>conclu&s;ion</HI> is of the <HI>e&s;&s;ence</HI> of the <HI>&s;yllogi&s;m?</HI><NOTE PLACE="marg">Affect.</NOTE> <NOTE PLACE="marg">Vexat.</NOTE></P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Longh.</SPEAKER>
<P><HI>No, no no.</HI> It is not about <HI>any &s;uch point;</HI> but <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word">. . .</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Nev.</SPEAKER>
<P>Whether the <HI>e&s;&s;ence</HI> of <HI>good</HI> is <HI>appet|ibility,</HI> or <HI>&s;uitablene&s;s.</HI><NOTE PLACE="marg">Affect.</NOTE></P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Longh.</SPEAKER>
<P>I am going to tell you my <HI>bu&s;ine&s;s,</HI><NOTE PLACE="marg">Vexat.</NOTE> if. . .</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Nev.</SPEAKER>
<P>You would know, perhaps,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Affect.</NOTE> if the <HI>good</HI> and the <HI>end</HI> are <HI>reciprocal?</HI></P>
</SP>
<SP>
